sentences.english: They needled their way through a primeval forest.

sentences.english: On Hubin Road, I walked alongside West Lake beneath swaying willow trees.

sentences.english: This is a clear through the dense forest in romantic fairy tale elves in the south.

sentences.english: I twisted through a maze of narrow corridors.
sentences.chinese: 我彎彎曲曲地穿行迷宮式的狹窄走廊。

sentences.english: During the lifetime, there will always be some dark tunnels for us to go through lonely.

sentences.english: The visible wind goes through freely in yours eye, this freedom is worth tracking down.

sentences.english: A tourist walks through snow-covered stelae at the Memorial to the Murdered Jews of Europe, also known as the Holocaust Memorial on December 2, 2010 in Berlin, Germany.

sentences.english: An oil tanker drove through Hengshan County, Shaanxi Province, China, Wednesday.
